Last Update Instructions – RTX Housing

We are currently working on a major upcoming update that will introduce new features and further improvements.

This update is primarily focused on fixing a compatibility issue related to model loading.

Important – Reason for This Update

Some servers experienced issues where shells or objects were not spawning correctly.

This was caused by inconsistent behavior of the native functions `IsModelInCdimage` and `IsModelValid`. On certain FiveM artifact versions, especially newer ones, these functions may return incorrect results for custom or streamed models.

Because of this, valid models were incorrectly rejected, which led to:

 Shells not spawning
 Objects failing to load
 Timeouts during loading
 Broken interiors or incomplete previews

Changes in This Update

The model loading system has been reworked to ensure consistent behavior across all servers.

 Removed `IsModelInCdimage` and `IsModelValid` as blocking checks
 Added proper timeout handling to prevent infinite loading loops
 Unified loading logic for shells, objects, and furniture

With these changes, model loading should now work correctly on all artifact versions and server configurations.


Installation Instructions

1. Replace the entire rtx_housing resource with the new version.
   Do not merge files. A full replacement is required to ensure everything works correctly.

2. Config folder:
   You may keep your existing config folder.

3. HTML folder:
   You can keep your entire html folder without any changes.

Additional Notes

 This update improves stability when spawning shells and objects.
 It reduces issues caused by invalid model detection.
 The system now behaves consistently across different server setups.
 Debug logging has been improved to help identify model loading issues.

Important Recommendation

After installing:

* Restart your server completely (not just the resource)

This update ensures stable and consistent model loading across all supported FiveM artifact versions.
